rule: Any
'package' should be separated from previous statement.
'{' should be on the previous line
First sentence of Javadoc is incomplete (period is missing) or not present.
Line contains a tab character.
Incorrect indentation level
tag should be placed immediately before the first word, with no space after.
tag should be preceded with an empty line.
'}' should be on the same line as the next part of a multi-block statement
Wrong lexicographical order for import
Line is longer than 100 characters
Missing a Javadoc comment.
Abbreviation in name must contain no more than '2' consecutive capital letters
Member name must match pattern '^[a-z][a-z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9]*$'
At-clause should have a non-empty description.
Whitespace around a symbol is not followed by whitespace
'(' is followed by whitespace.
')' is preceded with whitespace.
switch without "default" clause.
Whitespace around a symbol is not preceded by whitespace
Symbol should be on a new line
Overload methods should not be split

Empty line should be followed by

tag on the next line.
Top-level class BookmarkStack has to reside in its own source file.
'static' modifier out of order with the JLS suggestions.
Empty catch block.
'if' construct must use '{}'s.
'CTOR_DEF' should be separated from previous statement.
'else' construct must use '{}'s.
'for' construct must use '{}'s.
'protected' modifier out of order with the JLS suggestions.
Distance between variable declaration and its first usage is more than '3'
Javadoc comment has parse error.
GenericWhitespace '>' is followed by whitespace.
Local variable name must match pattern '^[a-z]([a-z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9]*)?$'
Each variable declaration must be in its own statement.
Catch parameter name 'eMissingResource' must match pattern '^[a-z]([a-z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9]*)?$'.
'public' modifier out of order with the JLS suggestions.
Array brackets at illegal position.
At-clauses have to appear in the order '[@param, @return, @throws, @deprecated]'.
Parameter must match pattern '^[a-z]([a-z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9]*)?$'
Single-line Javadoc comment should be multi-line.
'METHOD_DEF' should be separated from previous statement.

Redundant
